  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will test a modification of Cognitive Processing Therapy (CPT) for Post-Traumatic
      Stress Disorder, (PTSD) in which CPT is augmented with compensatory cognitive rehabilitation
      principles from the Cognitive Symptom Management and Rehabilitation Therapy (CogSMART)
      intervention to create a hybrid treatment, SMART-CPT. This study investigates the efficacy of
      SMART-CPT in improving PTSD and post-concussive symptoms, cognition, quality of life, and
      treatment compliance in those with a history of mild to moderate TBI and persistent cognitive
      complaints.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
